-- Haitians Blaming UN for Cholera Outbreak Burn 2 Police Posts, Kiskeya Says
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2010-11-15T19:31:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/haitians-blaming-un-for-cholera-outbreak-burn-2-police-posts-kiskeya-says.html
Haitians who claim U.N. peacekeeping
soldiers from Nepal were the cause of a cholera outbreak that
has killed nearly 1,000 set two police stations on fire after
clashing with authorities in a protest at a U.N. base, according
to  Radio Kiskeya .  The Port-Au-Prince-based radio station reported that U.N.
soldiers and Haitian police fired tear gas to disperse
protesters at the base in the northern city of Cap-Haitien,
Haiti’s second-largest city.  The  U.N. Stabilization Mission in Haiti  could not be
reached immediately for comment. The cholera outbreak has killed
917 with 14,642 hospitalizations, according to the Haitian
Health Ministry’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
